com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document

Class SpenObjectShape

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document.SpenObjectBase
      • com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document.SpenObjectShapeBase
        • com.samsung.android.sdk.pen.document.SpenObjectShape
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SpenObjectImage, SpenObjectTextBox

    public class SpenObjectShape
extends SpenObjectShapeBase
    Shape object class.
    ObjectShape is a class for shapes and a super class for images and textbox.
    It means this class has common properties and functions for shapes, images and textbox. For instance, properties and functions related to fill effect and form.
    Since:
    4.0.0

      • getFillEffect

        public void getFillEffect(SpenFillEffectBase effect)
        Get the fill effect.
        To get the fill effect, you should create a specific fill effect first.
        The type can be retained with getFillEffectType. 
         
    int effectType = shape.getFillEffectType();
    SpenFillEffectBase effect = SpenFillEffectBase.createFillEffect(effectType);

    if (effect != null) {
        shape.getFillEffect(effect);
    }
        Parameters:
        effect - (output) Fill effect to get.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the effect is null.
        Since:
        4.0.0
        See Also:
        SpenFillColorEffect, SpenFillImageEffect, SpenFillPatternEffect
